Package com.clouddevday

Class Summary
MyApp The MyApp Class is used to return a Application context for use in Classes that do not have access to the application context.
ParsedScheduleDataSet The ParseScheduleDataSet class is used to hold all of the parsed XML data about the schedule.
Presentation The Presentation class represents encapsulates the presenter, presentation title, and description for a given presentation.
PresentationActivity The PresentationActivity class is used to display the Presentation Description in a WebView container.
PresentationIterator The Presentation Iterator is used to implement the Iterator Design Pattern to allow iteration over the Presentation Objects in the application.
Presentations The class Presentations maintains a ArrayList of the Presentations in the Conference.

ScheduleActivity The Schedule Activity class extends ListActivity and displays the whole day schedule for the conference in a List Display.
ScheduleAdapter The ScheduleAdapter Class extends the ArrayAdapter and is a custom Adapter used by the ScheduleActivity class.
ScheduleDataHandler The ScheduleDataHandler class extends the SAX Parser DefaultHandler class for use in reading in Schedule Data from either a remote URL or the local data file.
ScheduleDataManager The ScheduleDataManager class is used to read in the Schedule Data at application start.
SplashScreenActivity The SplashScreenActivity Class is used to display the initial Splash Screen for the application.
Startup The Startup Class is used to initialize the Presentations class with data.
TimeSlotActivity The TimeSlotActivity class extends ListActivity and is responsible for filling in the individual TimeSlot tabs with the Room, Presenter and Presentation list items.
